# TrueCharts GitOps

**ALL cluster changes MUST go through Git.** Flux reconciles; do not mutate the live cluster.

## Workflow

1. Edit manifests / HelmReleases / config in the repo
2. Commit (and push) with a clear message
3. Monitor Flux: `kubectl get helmrelease`, `kubectl describe helmrelease`
4. Validate with `kubectl get` / `describe` / events only

## Never

- `kubectl apply`, `kubectl patch`, or any direct cluster edits
- Manual restarts (`kubectl rollout restart`), `kubectl scale`, or live resource edits

## Always

- Change files under `clusters/`, `repositories/`, etc.
- Let Flux deploy; use kubectl/flux only to **observe**
- After changes: check HelmRelease status, pods, and events

## Key paths

- `clusters/main/kubernetes/` — manifests and Helm releases
- `repositories/` — Helm repo definitions
- `clusters/main/talos/` — Talos config
- Dedicated image repos — see custom-images rule
- `clusters/main/clusterenv.yaml` — plaintext cluster/chart vars (encrypt via clustertool)
- Homelab **prose** docs — **nerd.dad** `docs/homelab/` → https://nerd.dad/latest/homelab/ (see homelab-docs rule)

## Tools

- **flux** v2.7.2 — deployment/reconciliation
- **talosctl** client v1.11.3 / server v1.11.2 — Talos OS
- **kustomize** — repo layout
- **clustertool** — Talos/Flux/SOPS wrapper (see clustertool rule)
- Charts: [TrueCharts common](https://truecharts.org/common/)
